  "prompt": "Why did Quora limit question details to 300 words?",
  "response": "Quora's decision to limit question details to 300 words likely stems from a desire to maintain the quality and clarity of the questions posed on the platform. Here are some potential reasons for this limit:\n\n1. **Clarity and Focus**: Shorter questions encourage users to be more concise and focused, which can help other users understand the core of the inquiry without getting lost in excessive detail.\n\n2. **Improved Engagement**: Limiting the length of questions may help increase user engagement by prompting users to think critically about what information is most essential to include, potentially leading to more thoughtful and relevant answers.\n\n3. **Enhanced User Experience**: A word limit can streamline the reading experience, making it quicker and easier for users to browse and interact with questions and answers.\n\n4. **Moderation and Management**: Shorter questions may be easier to moderate and manage, helping to ensure that the content remains high-quality and relevant to the community.\n\n5. **Preventing Spam and Low-Quality Content**: Limiting the length can deter users from posting overly complex or convoluted questions that may not add value to the community, reducing the likelihood of spam and low-quality content.\n\nBy implementing these limits, Quora aims to create a more efficient and effective platform for asking and answering questions.",
